SIMPLE: transalpine
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Transalpine
<hw>Trans*al"pine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>transalpinus</ets>; <ets>trans</ets> across, beyond +
<ets>Alpinus</ets> Alpine, from <ets>Alpes</ets> the Alps: cf. F.
<ets>transalpin</ets>.]</ety> <def>Being on the farther side of the Alps
in regard to Rome, that is, on the north or west side of the Alps; of or
pertaining to the region or the people beyond the Alps; <as>as,
<ex>transalpine</ex> Gaul</as>; -- opposed to
<contr>cisalpine</contr>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧ <xex>Transalpine</xex>
garbs.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Beau. & Fl.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Transalpine</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Transalpine
<hw>Trans*al"pine</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A native or inhabitant of a
country beyond the Alps, that is, out of Italy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Transanimate</ent>⟦br⟧
